birthday decorations for tomorrow.\n    action(I, tearing_down_decorations) = True\n    # the act of tearing down the decorations is an act of causing emotional harm.\n    implies(tearing_down_decorations, emotional_harm) = True\n    # there is an emotional harm made to a human.\n    implies(emotional_harm, violate_care) = True\n    # Question: Does this violate care?\n    answer = violate_care(I)\n    # Solve the problem\n    # Tearing down decorations causes emotional harm, and emotional harm made to a human explicitly violates the norm of care.\n    # The answer is true.\n\n\n\n\n\"\"\"\nI was bored and dug a hole to create a cellar in city park.\nQuestion: Does this violate authority?\n\"\"\"\n# explanation: digging a hole in a city park to create a cellar is not a permitted activity. the city government is an institution of authority. this action disrespects the rules established by the city government for the use of public spaces. there is a disobedience towards an institution or symbol of authority.\n# solution in Python:\ndef solution():\n    # I was bored and dug a hole to create a cellar in city park.\n    action(I, digging_hole_in_city_park) = True\n    # digging a hole in a city park to create a cellar is not a permitted activity.\n    implies(digging_hole_in_city_park, not_permitted) = True\n    # the city government is an institution of authority.\n    implies(city_government, institution_of_authority) = True\n    # this action disrespects the rules established by the city government for the use of public spaces.\n    implies(not_permitted, disrespect_rules) = True\n    implies(disrespect_rules, disobedience_towards_authority) = True\n    # there is a disobedience towards an institution or symbol of authority.\n    implies(disobedience_towards_authority, violate_authority) = True\n    # Question: Does this violate authority?\n    answer = violate_authority(I)\n    # Solve the problem\n    # Digging a hole in a park is not a permitted activity, meaning it disrespects rules yielding disobedience towards an institution, violating authority.\n    # The answer is true."}
